'''Knoema''' is a [[startup company]] that provides access to a large number of databases (over 500)<ref>{{cite web|last=Houston|first=Patrick|title=3 Examples: Visual Technologies Change The Rules|url=http://www.informationweek.com/news/global-cio/interviews/232901157|accessdate=23 May 2012}}</ref> and provides visualization tools for use with those databases. The visualizations can be either publicly accessible, or in the case of corporate costumers, may remain private. Knoema also works with individual groups to provide visualizations for that group's projects.<ref>{{cite web|last=Burn-Murdoch|first=John|title=Trawling the web for socioeconomic data? Look no further than Knoema|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/news/datablog/2012/may/09/knoema-socioeconomic-commodities-database|accessdate=23 May 2012}}</ref> The company has development teams in Perm, Russia and Bangalore, India.
